The report further highlights how Americans are struggling to afford their prescription drugs.
More from the report:Nearly 60 percent of adults aged 18 to 64 reported being prescribed medication over the past 12 months, as of 2017.
Women were more likely than men to ask for a lower-cost medication (22 percent vs. 16.4 percent).
More than 11 percent of adults did not take their medication as prescribed to try to reduce their costs, with women more likely than men to do so (12.7 percent vs. 9.7 percent).
Among the uninsured, 33.6 percent said they did not take their medicine as prescribed in an attempt to cut costs.